+We are building SherpaCarta — a luxurious, solemn digital Magna Carta for the 21st century. Current tech: React + Vite + Tailwind.
+Make it look extremely professional, authoritative, timeless and sacred — like a high-end printed constitutional document (think illuminated manuscript meets modern PDF).
+Requirements:
+
+Overall aesthetic: Deep oxblood/burgundy (#3c1e1e), aged parchment (#f5ede0 with subtle texture), 24k gold accents (#d4af88), dark ink. Use elegant serif fonts (Playfair Display for titles, EB Garamond or Crimson Text for body).
+Hero Header: Dramatic full-screen hero with large "SHERPACARTA" title, subtle wax seal / shield emblem, tagline "A Magna Carta for the Digital Age • Privacy First as a Right", and elegant buttons.
+Main Document Area: Make the entire thing look like a real multi-page PDF on parchment paper. Thick borders, drop shadow, subtle paper texture, page numbers, footer "Privacy is Sacred".
+Editable Content:
+Large, beautiful editable textarea for the Preamble.
+8+ collapsible or paginated chapters with rich, solemn content inspired by the 2011 Icelandic Constitution but adapted to digital rights and privacy-first principles.
+
+Navigation: Nice page dots + optional sidebar Table of Contents.
+Oath Modal: Very solemn, parchment-style modal with quill icon and "I Solemnly Affirm" button.
+Colors & Polish: Add more visual richness — gold borders, subtle gradients, better spacing, larger typography, decorative elements (horizontal rules, drop caps if possible).
+Performance & UX: Everything stays local (privacy-first). Auto-save drafts. Smooth transitions with framer-motion.
+Dependencies: Use lucide-react for icons, framer-motion, react-hot-toast.
+
+Make it feel important, eternal, and trustworthy. Go crazy good — dramatic but not kitschy. Prioritize elegance and authority.
+Current file is src/App.jsx. Rewrite it completely with the best version possible.

